						<h1>Moving Resources - Prohibited Items</h1>
						<p>Before your possessions are packed and loaded, it is important to understand which items cannot be shipped because they represent a hazard or are perishable. Listed below are some common, non-allowable items you will need to address prior to your pack and load dates.</p>
						<p><b>Hazardous Materials</b> &mdash; items that are flammable, corrosive or explosive.</p>
						<p>Examples include:</p>
						<p>
					  <table width="399" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="8">
								<tr>
									<td valign="top" width="133">
										<p>Sterno</p>
										<p>Matches</p>
										<p>Kerosene</p>
										<p>Gasoline</p>
										<p>Propane</p>
										<p>Fireworks</p>
										<p>Charcoal</p>
										<p>Charcoal Lighter</p>
										<p>Ammunition</p>
										<p>Ammunition reloading</p>
									</td>
									<td valign="top" width="133">
										<p>Lamp Oils</p>
										<p>Fire Extinguisher</p>
										<p>Aerosols</p>
										<p>Cleaning solvents</p>
										<p>Ammonia</p>
										<p>Nail polish</p>
										<p>Nail polish remover</p>
										<p>Liquid bleach</p>
										<p>Paints (latex, oil)</p>
									</td>
									<td valign="top" width="133">
										<p>Household batteries</p>
										<p>Chemistry sets</p>
										<p>Darkroom chemicals</p>
										<p>Pool chemicals</p>
										<p>Motor oil</p>
										<p>Car batteries</p>
										<p>Fertilizer</p>
										<p>Pesticides</p>
										<p>Poisons (weed killer, etc.)</p>
										<p>Paint thinner components</p>
									</td>
								</tr>
					  </table>
						</p>
						<p><b>Perishables</b> &mdash; food, plants or living things that may die or spoil in transit *</p>
						<p>Examples include:</p>
						<p>
					  <table width="399" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="8">
								<tr>
									<td valign="top" width="133">
										<p>Frozen food</p>
										<p>Refrigerated Foods</p>
									</td>
									<td valign="top" width="133">
										<p>Produce</p>
										<p>Plants</p>
									</td>
									<td valign="top" width="133">
										<p>Open foods</p>
										<p>Foods without adequate preservation</p>
									</td>
								</tr>
					  </table>
						</p>
						<p><i>* You should empty your refrigerators and freezers and keep appliance doors 	open for at least 24 hours in advance of loading. This will allow appliances to dry 	out and prevent the growth of mold.</i></p>
						<p><b>Items of Personal Importance or Sentimental Value</b> &mdash; These items can create problems should your shipment be delayed or items lost. We suggest that 	irreplaceable items and/or sentimental items be carried with you instead of being 	packed with your shipment.</p>
						<p>Examples include:</p>
						<p>
					  <table width="399" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="8">
								<tr>
									<td valign="top" width="133">
										<p>Airline tickets</p>
										<p>Car keys</p>
										<p>Cell phones</p>
										<p>Pagers</p>
										<p>Laptop computers</p>
										<p>Checkbooks</p>
										<p>School records</p>
									</td>
									<td valign="top" width="133">
										<p>Certificates of deposit</p>
										<p>Stocks</p>
										<p>Bonds</p>
										<p>IRAs</p>
										<p>Financial documents</p>
										<p>Deeds</p>
										<p>Medical/dental records	Insurance policies</p>
									</td>
									<td valign="top" width="133">
										<p>Prescription medicine</p>
										<p>Computer disks</p>
										<p>Address books</p>
										<p>Jewelry</p>
										<p>Family photographs/albums</p>
										<p>Cash</p>
									</td>
								</tr>
					  </table>
						</p>
